definitions.definition: Relating to time, or units of time.
examples: He is 67 in chronological age, but has the mind and body of someone 55.

definitions.definition: In order of time from the earliest to the latest .
examples: The live report lists all the events in chronological order.

subdefinitions.definition: Relating to the arrangement of events in the order in which they occur within a story , rather than the order in which they are released .

main_definition: Relating to time, or units of time.
secondary_definitions: In order of time from the earliest to the latest .
